Biography

2019: 33 starts and 36 appearances overall … belted four home runs and registered seven doubles, a triple, and 19 RBI’s … committed just three errors on the season for a fielding percentage of .991 … threw out 14 would be base stealers out of 37 total attempts … drove in three runs and had two doubles during 4-0 win at Hawai’i (Feb. 17) … went 3-for-5 with a home run, a triple, and three RBI’s as the Pilots won at Seattle U (Apr. 2) … had a career day during win at USD (Apr. 20) when he left the yard twice, collected six RBI’s, and finished with three hits; two homers matches a program record for home runs in a game, and his six RBI’s are tied for fourth most.

2018: 17 starts and 20 appearances behind the plate … collected 13 hits, two homers, a double, nine RBI’s and 10 runs scored … belted a home run and finished with a pair of hits during 8-0 win over St. Joes (Feb. 23) … launched a three-run homer and finished with four RBI’s as the Pilots topped Saint Mary’s (Mar. 16).

2017: 25 starts and 29 overall appearances at catcher and DH … hit .264 with three home runs, a triple, three doubles, 11 RBI’s and 10 runs scored … first career hit came in first career appearances at CSUN (Feb. 19) … hit homers in back-to-back games against Oregon (May 9) and at BYU (May 11) … that BYU game he went 4-for-6 with three RBI’s and three runs scored.

LAKERIDGE HS: Earned four letters for the Pacers … 2016 Oregon 6A State Player of the Year after batting .565 as a senior … also landed first-team all-state and was the 2016 All-Three Rivers League Player of the Year as he helped lead the Pacers to the second round of the state playoffs … belted four homers during his senior campaign and tallied 12 doubles, two triples and 31 RBI’s, while boasting a slugging percentage of .921 and an OPS of 1.578 … was a three-time selection to the All-Three Rivers League First Team and he was chosen to play in the Oregon 6A/5A All-Star Series … he earned second-team all-state as a junior in 2015 after garnering honorable all-state as a sophomore … he previously nabbed all-league honorable mention during his freshman season.

PERSONAL: Born on Jan. 20, 1998 in Portland, Ore. … parents are Jennifer and Stephen Elske … major is accounting.
